text:
A few thousand votes uncovered in Georgia’s recount narrowly cut into Biden’s margin but didn’t reverse his lead.

Still, an official says it shows the “irony” of Trump’s false claims of a fraudulent audit: “He has gained in the finding of these votes.”  https://t.co/vM0W1JwzJa

As Thanksgiving break approaches, many colleges are seeing spikes in coronavirus infections. For help, some campuses are turning to students to work the phones as contact tracers.

text:
Preliminary results show Sinovac's vaccine produces an immune response — but it's too early to say whether it prevents disease. 

Hundreds of thousands of people in China have already received the shot.

name: NPR
text:
Put a pin in it. 
Circle back. 
I'll loop you in. 
Deep dive. 

Belittled and unloved, corporate jargon endures — even thrives.

Social scientists say the use of such phrases is often tied to where people stand in a social hierarchy.
